<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Arabella Del Busso was doing what she does best on Sunday - showing off her incredible figure. </p>

<p>The 30-year-old model shared an Instagram Stories post in which she posed in black underwear and a pair of fishnet stockings. </p>

<p>She added a cropped black shirt that sat off her shoulders and featured a large metallic graphic print.  </p>

<p>Looking good: Arabella Del Busso (pictured) was doing what she does best on Sunday - showing off her incredible figure. The 30-year-old model shared an Instagram Stories post in which she posed in black underwear and a pair of fishnet stockings</p>

<p>A pair of white sneakers were added to the ensemble, and the brunette wore her dark hair down around her shoulders.  </p>

<p>On Wednesday, NRL star Josh Reynolds' ex-girlfriend showed off her latest transformation after getting new hair extensions.</p>

<p>The model shared a photo to Instagram, after visiting Sake Hair Studio in Melbourne.</p>

<p>Loves her fashion! She is no stranger to showing off her eclectic looks online </p>

<p>Arabella wore a full face of makeup for the picture, including foundation, rosy blush, and black eyeliner.</p>

<p>'Thank you Sake Hair Studio for the amazing weft extensions... they are safe for your natural hair and are applied without heat,' she wrote.</p>

<p>She explained: 'They last up to around 6-8 weeks... and they've given myself just that extra bit of thickness and length.'</p>

<p>New hair, don't care! On Wednesday, NRL star Josh Reynolds' ex-girlfriend showed off her latest transformation after getting new hair extensions</p>

<p>Arabella's post comes after it was announced she'll be appearing on Channel Seven's upcoming series SAS Australia.</p>

<p>The military-style show will see the contestants having to endure sleep deprivation, interrogation techniques and physical challenges.</p>

<p>The lingerie model will be joined by a growing list of celebrities including convicted drug smuggler Schapelle Corby and publicist Roxy Jacenko. </p>

<p>SAS Australia premieres in October on Channel Seven </p>

